Section 1:
Act 280 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 SENATE BILL 294
4
5 By: Senator K. Hammer
6 By: Representative Underwood
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING ELECTION AUDITS;
10 TO ALLOW THE STATE BOARD OF ELECTION COMMISSIONERS TO
11 AUDIT A COUNTY IN THE PRECEDING ELECTION IN CERTAIN
12 CIRCUMSTANCES; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
13
14
Subtitle
15
16 TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING ELECTION
17 AUDITS; AND TO ALLOW THE STATE BOARD OF
18 ELECTION COMMISSIONERS TO AUDIT A COUNTY
19 IN THE PRECEDING ELECTION IN CERTAIN
20 CIRCUMSTANCES.
21
22 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
23
24 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 7-4-121(a)(2)(A), concerning the duties of
25 the State Board of Election Commissioners during a post-election audit, is
26 amended to read as follows:
27 (A)(i) Except as otherwise provided in subdivision
28 (a)(2)(A)(ii) of this section, Select select by lot the counties, polling
29 sites, early voting locations, and vote centers to be audited.
30 (ii) If a county in the immediately preceding
31 preferential primary election or general election is found to have less than
32 one hundred percent (100%) accuracy in the State Board of Election
33 Commissioners audit, the county shall be chosen for audit in the subsequent
34 preferential primary election or general election;
35 APPROVED: 3/12/25
36
